-! # how to errors: 012-delimiters-open-paren-unmatched.zo
-!
-! @cmd: `zo build 012-delimiters-open-paren-unmatched.zo`
-!
-! A program is like a conversation. When you open a parenthesis `(`, 
-! you are starting a new sub-thought. 
-!
-! If you never close it with a `)`, zo is left hanging. It doesn't 
-! know where your thought ends and the next one begins. This is an 
-! "Unmatched" error.

fun main() {
  -- Mistake: We opened a group but never closed it.
  imu result := (10 + 5;
  
  showln(result);
}

-! ## the diagnostic map.
-!
-! zo points to the exact `(` that is lonely. Because it hit a 
-! semicolon `;` (the end of the statement) before finding a `)`, 
-! it knows the structure is broken.
-!
-! ## try this.
-!
-!   1. Finish the thought: add a `)` after the `5`.
-!   2. Try leaving a brace `{` open. Notice how the error message changes to
-!      reflect the different shape of the delimiter.

-- EXPECTED OUTPUT:
-- [E0019] Error: Unmatched opening delimiter
--     ╭─[ 012-delimiters-open-paren-unmatched.zo:14:17 ]
--     │
--  14 │   imu result := (10 + 5;
--     │                 ┬
--     │                 ╰── this delimiter has no matching closing delimiter
--     │
--  17 │ }
--     │ ┬
--     │ ╰── this closing delimiter skipped over it
--     │
--     │ Help: Add the corresponding closing delimiter
--     │
--     │ Note: Every opening delimiter must be closed by its matching partner.
--     │       `(` with `)`, `[` with `]`, `{` with `}`
-- ────╯
